I wasn't asleep.

499
00:47:06,907 --> 00:47:08,575
Not in bed, yet!

500
00:47:08,576 --> 00:47:10,827
And doing naughty stuff, too!

501
00:47:10,828 --> 00:47:13,572
Come, dearie, we're going home!

502
00:47:13,706 --> 00:47:15,790
Kidnapped by a cop, no less!

503
00:47:15,791 --> 00:47:17,158
<i>Lemme go!</i>

504
00:47:17,168 --> 00:47:19,544
<i>- Ah, it's you! - Let her go!
- I'm gonna report you.</i>

505
00:47:19,545 --> 00:47:22,797
<i>Camille didn't want to go to your house.
I think she has her reasons.</i>

506
00:47:22,798 --> 00:47:26,551
<i>I'll file a formal complaint!
Come along. - Don't wanna!</i>

507
00:47:26,552 --> 00:47:28,750
<i>The judge will vindicate me.</i>

508
00:48:06,842 --> 00:48:11,213
I don't think it was a good idea.
I'm getting hallucinations.

509
00:48:11,222 --> 00:48:13,215
These fries are talking to me.

510
00:48:13,224 --> 00:48:18,144
And what are they telling you?
"Eat me, eat me, Fatso!"

511
00:48:18,145 --> 00:48:20,013
What's going on here?

512
00:48:20,022 --> 00:48:21,523
You're not eating?

513
00:48:21,524 --> 00:48:22,971
Isn't it good?

514
00:48:24,276 --> 00:48:27,612
We're on a hunger strike,
until Camille returns.

515
00:48:27,613 --> 00:48:30,141
Camille will come back.

516
00:48:30,616 --> 00:48:35,146
She's coming to see the judge who'll
decide, if her aunt may keep her or not.

517
00:48:45,005 --> 00:48:46,372
<i>Dear Camille,</i>

518
00:48:46,382 --> 00:48:49,501
<i>since you left,
it hasn't been much fun.</i>

519
00:48:49,635 --> 00:48:53,756
<i>We tried having a hunger strike,
but it didn't work.</i>

520
00:48:54,765 --> 00:48:58,009
<i>The Beatrice's mother came.</i>

521
00:49:03,315 --> 00:49:05,388
<i>She hid herself in Rosie's arms.</i>

522
00:49:06,193 --> 00:49:07,810
<i>I wanna stay with you.</i>

523
00:49:08,279 --> 00:49:11,432
<i>And Ahmed peed the bed again.</i>

524
00:49:23,794 --> 00:49:25,787
What...

525
00:49:33,179 --> 00:49:35,673
<i>One, two... One, two.</i>

526
00:49:35,931 --> 00:49:40,101
<i>This is Simon.
If you can hear me, raise your arm.</i>

527
00:49:40,102 --> 00:49:42,812
<i>No, the other one.</i>

528
00:49:42,813 --> 00:49:45,090
<i>Sorry, I couldn't resist the gag.</i>

529
00:49:45,357 --> 00:49:47,976
<i>Everything's going very badly.</i>

530
00:49:48,486 --> 00:49:51,730
<i>So, listen carefully...</i>

531
00:49:58,245 --> 00:50:00,989
You're just like your mother,
you little slut.

532
00:50:01,081 --> 00:50:03,950
But your nonsense suits my purposes,
you know? - It's Camille!

533
00:50:03,959 --> 00:50:06,327
The judge won't like it.

534
00:50:06,595 --> 00:50:10,064
You've dug your own grave,
you poor excuse for a girl.

535
00:50:22,269 --> 00:50:25,271
Your Honor, I'll give her
an excellent education,

536
00:50:25,272 --> 00:50:29,393
a healthy environment, comfort
and above all, love.

537
00:50:29,777 --> 00:50:32,475
I love her like my own daughter.

538
00:50:34,031 --> 00:50:37,025
<i>And Camille and I,
get along so well!</i>

539
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:40,845
She doesn't seem
wildly enthusiastic.

540
00:50:40,846 --> 00:50:44,499
You must understand her.
After the tragedy which struck her,

541
00:50:44,500 --> 00:50:47,894
she must have the impression
of betraying her poor mother.

542
00:50:50,506 --> 00:50:56,254
Camille, what do you think?
Would you like to live with your aunt?

543
00:50:56,262 --> 00:51:00,124
You can see, after this incident,
why I have concerns

544
00:51:00,141 --> 00:51:04,670
about her safety in this place,
whose lax methods leave much to be desired.

545
00:51:05,396 --> 00:51:07,772
<i>You're just like your mother,
you little slut.</i>

546
00:51:07,773 --> 00:51:10,066
<i>Running off with a boy
at your age, ! For shame!</i>

547
00:51:10,067 --> 00:51:11,935
<i>The foster home is unable
to supervise you.</i>

548
00:51:11,944 --> 00:51:13,778
<i>The judge won't like that.</i>

549
00:51:13,779 --> 00:51:14,904
Gimme that!

550
00:51:14,905 --> 00:51:17,057
Stop, stop!

551
00:51:17,183 --> 00:51:20,461
<i>You've dug your own grave,
you poor excuse for a girl.</i>

552
00:51:33,382 --> 00:51:36,535
- What are you dressed up as, Alice?
- As a pirate.

553
00:51:36,885 --> 00:51:39,788
- What about you?
- As a Mummy.

554
00:51:39,930 --> 00:51:43,141
- What are you dressed up as, Beatrice?
- As Camille.

555
00:51:43,142 --> 00:51:46,352
So, Super Zucchini, what are your superpowers?
Do you make vegetables grow fast?

556
00:51:46,353 --> 00:51:49,105
What are you dressed as?
As a lame brain?

557
00:51:49,106 --> 00:51:51,554
Remind me again, who saved you?

558
00:51:51,734 --> 00:51:53,735
He's dressed up as a cop.

559
00:51:53,736 --> 00:51:56,309
Careful, Monsieur,
I still don't like cops.

560
00:51:56,488 --> 00:51:58,731
But I'll keep the hat.

561
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:20,044
- When will you come back?
- Soon.

562
00:52:20,220 --> 00:52:22,088
How soon?

563
00:52:22,973 --> 00:52:26,718
You know, Courgette,
I spoke to the judge.

564
00:52:27,645 --> 00:52:31,515
I spoke to him because I'd like to be
your host family...

565
00:52:31,649 --> 00:52:34,302
you and Camille.

566
00:52:34,401 --> 00:52:37,600
- Does that mean we're your guests?
- Yes.

567
00:52:37,863 --> 00:52:41,532
And you'll be like our family,
Even though you're all alone?

568
00:52:41,533 --> 00:52:42,650
That's it.

569
00:52:42,785 --> 00:52:46,037
You'll come live at the house.

570
00:52:46,038 --> 00:52:48,486
My home. I mean YOUR home.

571
00:52:48,832 --> 00:52:50,484
If you want to.

572
00:52:51,251 --> 00:52:55,872
- Does Camille know?
- Yes, the judge spoke to her.

573
00:52:57,883 --> 00:53:00,957
What did she say?

574
00:53:01,261 --> 00:53:05,014
I don't know. But you have time
to think about it.

575
00:53:05,015 --> 00:53:07,713
You and Camille. Hm?

576
00:53:08,060 --> 00:53:11,259
Voila. See you soon, big guy.

577
00:53:12,189 --> 00:53:14,262
<i>See you soon, Raymond.</i>

578
00:53:33,168 --> 00:53:37,038
I want to thank you all,
for saving my life.

579
00:53:37,047 --> 00:53:40,792
Especially Simon. Thank you.

580
00:53:41,677 --> 00:53:44,171
I never thought,

581
00:53:44,555 --> 00:53:49,058
life could be so cool.
With you it's really cool.

582
00:53:49,059 --> 00:53:52,228
- We'll be together, all our lives!
- Cool!

583
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:55,106
No, it's not true. We won't
be together, all our lives.

584
00:53:55,107 --> 00:53:58,852
Camille and Courgette are splitting.
And with the cop, too!

585
00:54:21,717 --> 00:54:24,085
Hey, Simon.

586
00:54:26,346 --> 00:54:28,589
Simon.

587
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:32,878
We won't leave, Simon.

588
00:54:33,145 --> 00:54:36,094
We wanna stay here.

589
00:54:37,399 --> 00:54:41,770
It wouldn't be right to leave.
We're fine here, all together.

590
00:54:43,155 --> 00:54:45,649
Simon...

591
00:54:51,163 --> 00:54:53,736
You must go away.

592
00:54:59,505 --> 00:55:04,331
You've no idea how rare it is
for people to adopt kids as old as us.

593
00:55:05,886 --> 00:55:09,005
- But...
- No. You must go, for our sake.

594
00:55:12,351 --> 00:55:14,549
Understand?

595
